@adiessl thanks for contacting us.

The behavior you are seeing is by design. You are adding the metadata directly to the endpoint. When you hit `/Counter` it goes through the fallback route `MapFallbackToPage`. 

The way to achieve what you want is to put the authorize attribute directly on the `_Host.cshtml` page using `@attribute [Authorize(...)]`

